# Swordjin Godot Development Progress

## Current Build Info
- Engine: Godot 4.4.1-stable (GL Compatibility)
- Target: Mobile PWA via HTML5 export
- Resolution: 640x360 (scales to mobile)

# v0.53 — Floating Health Bars

### New Files
- `scenes/ui/health_bar.tscn` + `scripts/health_bar.gd` — Reusable health bar UI
  - Small bar (32×6px) that sits above characters
  - Green → yellow → red color shift as HP drops
  - Smooth width scaling based on current/max HP

### Updated
- `scenes/player.tscn` — added HealthBar instance
- `scenes/skeleton.tscn` — added HealthBar instance
- `scenes/skeleton_captain.tscn` — added HealthBar instance
- `scenes/skeleton_archer.tscn` — added HealthBar instance
- `scripts/player.gd` — calls `health_bar.update_health()` in `_ready()` and `_update_label()`
- `scripts/skeleton.gd` — calls `health_bar.update_health()` in `_update_label()`
- `scripts/skeleton_captain.gd` — calls `health_bar.update_health()` in `_update_label()`
- `scripts/skeleton_archer.gd` — calls `health_bar.update_health()` in `_update_label()`

### Visual Polish
- Health bars appear above all combatants (player + 3 enemy types)
- Color-coded: green (>60%), yellow (30-60%), red (<30%)
- Enemy labels still show text HP + shield count (captain)

### Zero Parse Errors ✅
